## placement of locked areas on mounting surfaces

there are two types of locked areas:

     * locked areas for placement
     * locked areas for cutouts

locked areas are always rectangular.

the following specifications can be used for the placement.

parameters | parameter type | usage | syntax | example  
---|---|---|---|---  
dimension | dimension | size of locked area |  =list{width, height} |  =list{60.0, 120.0}  
coordinate | coordinate | position on the mounting surface |  =list{  
<x-coordinate>,  
<y-coordinate>  
} |  =list{  
150.6,  
70.2  
}  
plug | plug | plug-socket principle |  ='plugname' |  =planefront_mountingpanel_s1  
position | string or integer | position within the sequence in a hierarchy level of the project |  position as string: ='<position>' position as integer: =<position> |  position as string:='2' position as integer:=2  
additional specifications | supplementarymap |  type of locked area. 1 = locked area for the placement 2 = locked area for a cutout |  locked area: =map{  
pair{'type', 1}  
} cutout: =map{  
pair{'type', 2}  
} |  locked area: =map{  
pair{'type', 1}  
} cutout: =map{  
pair{'type', 2}  
}

## placement of busbar systems on the mounting surface

in order to position a busbar system that consists of at least two holders and two busbars, the length, start position, number of holders and the relative positions of the first and last holders are required.

you specify the length and start position with the dimension and coordinate parameters.

you specify the number of supports as well as the positions of the first and last supports with the supplementarymap parameter.

you enter the value of the endoffset parameter as a negative number, since the offset relative to the end of the busbar system has to be calculated.

example:

=map{  
pair{'holder',3},  
pair{'startoffset',20.0},  
pair{'endoffset',-20.0}  
}

further supports are placed evenly distributed over the length of the busbar system.

the following specifications can be used for the placement.

